  </string>
  <string id="st_pda_ic_loner_2_outcome_3">
      <text>chance:40:spawn_hostile:bandit:90</text>
  </string>


EXAMPLE 3: Friendly Duty member with location-based job (multi-turn)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  Preconditions: req_npc_friendly:dolg,req_npc_rank:experienced,req_rank:trainee
  (Friendly Duty NPC, at least experienced rank, player is at least trainee)

  Turn 1: NPC mentions a location, player decides to help or not.
  Turn 2: If player agrees, NPC gives details and marks the location.

  NOTE: This example shows how to use smart terrain placeholders with watch_location_trigger
  to create mini-jobs that send the player to a real location with real consequences.

